      • onArmSync

        public void onArmSync(Myo myo,
                      long timestamp,
                      Arm arm,
                      XDirection xDirection,
                      float rotation,
                      WarmupState warmupState)
        Called when a paired Myo recognizes that it is on an arm.
        Parameters:
        myo - The Myo for this event.
        timestamp - The timestamp of when the event is received by the SDK. Timestamps are 64 bit unsigned integers that correspond to a number of microseconds since some (unspecified) period in time.
        arm - The identified Arm of myo.
        xDirection - The identified XDirection of myo.
        rotation - The estimated rotation of Myo on the user's arm after a sync.
        warmupState - The warmup state of myo. If warmupState is equal to WarmupState.warmupStateCold, onWarmupCompleted(Myo, long, WarmupResult) will be called when the warmup period has completed.

      • onBatteryLevelReceived

        public void onBatteryLevelReceived(Myo myo,
                                   long timestamp,
                                   byte level)
        Called when a paired Myo receives a battery level update.

        Updates occur when the battery level changes and when the battery level is explicitly requested.

        Note: Technically, the parameter level is an unsigned 8 bit integer. However, as the maximum battery level is 100, this detail can be ignored.

        Parameters:
        myo - The Myo for this event.
        timestamp - The timestamp of when the event is received by the SDK. Timestamps are 64 bit unsigned integers that correspond to a number of microseconds since some (unspecified) period in time.
        level - The battery level reported by the myo; the value is a number from 0 to 100 representing the percentage of battery life remaining.
        See Also:
        Myo.requestBatteryLevel()
